<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - Install - Grille / Shroud</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Grille / Shroud</title>
        <para>Prior to installing the grille and shroud assembly, inspect the mounting tabs on the inner upper surface
            of the shroud (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0901067">Figure 76</hotlnk>). Insure that all tabs are functional and in place.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0901067" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901067.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 76. Grille / Shroud Tab and Mounting Hole Inspection</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the hood in the closed position, align the four (4) upper mounting holes and tabs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert tabs on shroud assembly into mounting holes (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_22.xml" xrefid="f0901021">Figure 31, Item 1</hotlnk>) on hood assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the lower grille/shroud mounting holes (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_22.xml" xrefid="f0901021">Figure 31, Item 2</hotlnk>) with tabs on cross bar.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the four mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_22.xml" xrefid="f0901021">Figure 31, Item 3</hotlnk>) in the assembly and
                tighten.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recheck for grille and shroud proper fit and alignment.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten to 3 to 3.3 LBF-FT (4 to 4.5 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>Do not overtighten the mounting screws.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
